  Systemd.service(5) - System and service manager
  Systemd.service(5)

  1. Description

  Systemd is a system and service manager for Linux, compatible with
  SysV and LSB init scripts.

  Systemd can work as a drop-in replacement for sysvinit. It can
  automatically start a set of services, and shut them down cleanly on
  shutdown.

